summary: This is a U.S. Department of Justice foreign travel questionnaire for an Assistant U.S. Attorney from the Southern District of New York traveling to Stockholm, Sweden from February 3-6, 2020. The purpose is to interview a Swedish witness named Jane Doe in the ongoing, sensitive investigation of Jeffrey Epstein, with Ghislaine Maxwell identified as a subject.

keyFacts: The document is a foreign travel authorization for an SDNY AUSA to travel to Stockholm, Sweden from February 3-6, 2020 to interview a witness in the Jeffrey Epstein case.
The case is identified as "In re Jeffrey Epstein, USAO # 2018R01618" and is described as an ongoing and very sensitive investigation.
Ghislaine Maxwell is explicitly named as a subject of the investigation, with her citizenship noted as U.S., U.K., and French.
The witness to be interviewed is identified as "Jane Doe, Swedish," indicating international cooperation in the Epstein investigation.
The travel involves coordination with foreign authorities who have cleared the visit and are prepared to cooperate.
